<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n22051f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22051f">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22051f"> 51(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> best pleased</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">And during all this talk she did not forget to practise little tricks: sometimes she would knock his elbow when he was writing; another time she threw gravel and spoiled his work, so that he was forced to write it all over again. Another time also she recommenced these tricks, and took away his paper and parchment, so that he could not work,&mdash;at which he was not best pleased, fearing that his master would be angry. <small> Robert B. Douglas, trans., <a name="RBDM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBDM"><cite title="source">ONE HUNDRED MERRIE AND DELIGHTSOME STORIES</cite></a> (1923) Story 23</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
